    "backgrounds": [
      {
        "name": "Status",
        "focus": "Camarilla",
        "value": 3,
        "notes": "",
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Status",
        "focus": "Clan Tremere",
        "value": 1,
        "notes": [
          "As a result of his shady history as the founder of a minor House with a bad reputation and for his time as a \"double agent\" in the Sabbat, many of his Clan look at him with suspicion for his seeming lack of loyalty to the ideals of the Pyramid.",
          "Despite this, his 3 centuries in the Clan still commands respect."
        ],
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Herd",
        "focus": "Court Prisoners",
        "value": 2,
        "notes": [
          "There is said to be a hidden room within Casa Loma creatively titled \"Room 101\" where it is said that Thin-bloods are sent to when found by the new Sheriff. Despite the rumors nobody knows what this room looks like except for the victims already trapped there. And who in the Camarilla would speak up for a Duskborn?",
          "During the conflict for Praxis, Black Caesar populated his dungeon with two members of the Moon Club, which he seized under false pretenses."
        ],
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Mawla",
        "focus": "Baron's Bleak Bokor",
        "value": 2,
        "notes": [
          "Caesar and the Bokor both had a hand in shaping what Kindred society would look like in the Caribbean when they both meddled in the Haitian Revolution. Neither man asked too many questions about the other's \"boss\".",
          "They were also both founding members of House High Saturday, with the Samedi's involvement being crucial for their understanding of Necromancy. He may not be a member today, but is still on good terms with Caesar."
        ],
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Contact",
        "focus": "Christopher Giovanni Jr.",
        "value": 2,
        "notes": [
          "29 year old \"made man\" who just received the Proxy Kiss but is stuck with cooking the books for the family.",
          "Forced to serve as the middle man between Caesar and Bacchus, which he hates because both men scare him.",
          "Still does his job dutifully because he wants to get Embraced while he's still good-looking."
        ],
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Retainer",
        "focus": "Jean Ducheski-Francois III",
        "value": 2,
        "notes": [
          "Jean and his family are the culmination of 100 years of Caesar's work to make his own personal mystic soldiers.",
          "The patriarch himself is mild-mannered and charming with the air of an academic. Much older than he looks."
        ],
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Retainer",
        "focus": "Jezdimir Ducheski",
        "value": 1,
        "notes": [
          "Despite hailing from the Ducheski stronghold in Poland, Jezdimir has little knowledge on his family's purpose.",
          "Looks and acts like an Eastern European hooligan; his petty criminal background is a surprising asset in redwork."
        ],
        "source": {
          "book": "",
          "page": 0
        }
      }
    ],
