        "era": "A Time of Lineage",
        "startYear": 1804,
        "endYear": 1860,
        "affiliation": "camarilla",
        "details": "During the period after the Haitian Revolution, what would become House High Saturday begins to unify and formalize their interactions with \"the Lwa\". They skirt around the laws of the Tremere regarding teaching outsiders but the reward outweighs the risk. Caesar is assisted by a small group of clanmates, but also his Ducheski revenants and even a member of the burgeoning Samedi bloodline: the Bokor, who is instrumental to the House's understanding of Necromancy.\n\n\"Times are changing, brothers and sisters! Let us walk into this future of radiant moonlight hand in hand with gods old and new!\"",
        "locations": [
          "Port-au-Prince, Haiti",
          "Sailing the Oceans"
        ]
      },
      {
        "era": "A Time of Excess",
        "startYear": 1871,
        "endYear": 1919,
        "affiliation": "camarilla",
        "details": "Counting up all the profits from his bloody work for Jervais makes Caesar both powerful in the mortal world and within the Pyramid as he is promoted to Magister while he continues his spy work for Goratrix. As he looks at the state of his people in the Americas, he begins to grow disillusioned with his role in vampiric society. Busywork takes him from the Americas to the Prime Chantry in Vienna to report his earnings and discoveries to the Council of Seven.\n\n\"Of course, my lord. Magister Caesar bani Gwo-samdi lives to serve. I would like to make a report regarding a most intriguing Malkavian I met...\"",
        "locations": [
          "Florida, USA",
          "Louisiana, USA",
          "Vienna, Austria"
        ]
      },
      {
        "era": "Interlude",
        "startYear": 1919,
        "endYear": 1930,
        "affiliation": "camarilla",
        "details": "On orders to assist Carna, the new Regent of Milwaukee, Caesar is sent as a mercenary from the Council to fight against the Lupine horde threatening to siege the city. He forms a bond with the new Prince who fought on the front lines: Terrence Merik. Saving an Apprentice by the name of Mortius from final death at the hands of a werewolf, Caesar is given a Life Boon.",
        "locations": [
          "Vienna, Austria",
          "Milwaukee, USA"
        ]
      },
      {
        "era": "A Time of Faith",
        "startYear": 1930,
        "endYear": 1998,
        "affiliation": "sabbat",
        "details": "Having a full breakdown, Black Caesar makes a complete turn to the Sabbat when he pursued his sire Jervais to Toledo and openly murders him. No longer abiding by the Masquerade or his spy act, he is spurred further into the Sword of Caine's philosophy as he believes the Lwa have left him without their blessings which leaves him searching for meaning within House Goratrix not just as an infiltrator but as one of their war-time leaders in Canada.\n\n\"Lilith awakened Caine... and yet we are expected to remain asleep, our eyes shut to the injustice of this profane, kine-ruled world. No more. No. More.\"",
        "locations": [
